CM_ BO_ 35 "STEERING WHEEL ANGLE  $xxxx????0000 - steering wheel angle*0.5  Each increment or decrement represents 0.5 degrees. One complete turn of the wheel would be $2D0 (720) units of change.   typical range of values: $14FF – extreme left $1000 – center $0AFF – extreme right $3FFF – offline (uninitialized) As a vehicle develops alignment issues, be aware that center may move away from $1000.  STEERING WHEEL DRIVER TORQUE  $????xxxx0000 – turning force by driver -- OR rate of turn  A measurement of how ";
CM_ BO_ 37 "ENGINE VARIABLES  $xxxx???????? – mass air flow sensor?  Unsigned word (values $0000-$1540) Typical idle value: $62A low at idle and while braking goes higher when accelerating  $????xxxx???? – manifold air pressure?  Signed word ($06FE-$0EAD) (zero at $07ff, most typical value is $0763)  $????????xxxx – engine torque?  Signed word (zero at $07ff, most typical value near $07ff) Increases with engine torque  Numbers appear to be analog values which clearly respond while driving, but their purpose";
CM_ BO_ 38 "ENGINE / Readiness $xxxx???????? - Engine output power ? $?????x?????? - Ready to Drive State ? $???????x???? - Engine Status ?";
CM_ BO_ 39 "UNKNOWN VEHICLE PARAMETERS  $xxxx????0000 – unknown  Number centered around $8B7F  $????xxxx0000 – unknown  Signed word (zero at $07ff) Values seen: $0744 - $0910  Numbers appear to be analog values which clearly respond while driving, but their purpose is unknown. The final two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 40 " 0,1 unknown 2,3 unknown 4,5 unknown";
CM_ BO_ 43 "ROLL/PITCH/YAW  $xxxx???????? – vehicle roll (tilt left/right) $????xxxx???? – vehicle pitch (nose up/down) $????????xxxx – vehicle yaw (rate of turn)  See notes column (to the right) for usage information and experimental values.";
CM_ BO_ 47 "UNKNOWN VARIABLE (BRAKING?)  $000000000xxx???? – value $000000000???xx?? – unknown $000000000?????xx – unknown   The first variable might be a signed number with $11A representing a zero or neutral value.";
CM_ BO_ 53 "AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION  $x??????????? -- transmission status bitmap $?xxx???????? – transmission speed 1 $????x??????? -- transmission status bitmap $?????xxx???? – transmission speed 2 $????????xxxx – transmission status bitmap  Units of measurement are unknown. Subtract 2004 from both speeds values. The last two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 55 "UNKNOWN  $xxxx0000???? – unknown, word $????0000xxxx – unknown, word  Both variables may be signed numbers where $1FFF represents zero.   The last two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 113 "UNKNOWN  $xxxx0000??00 – value, word $????0000xx00 – bitmap, byte  The first variable has a zero point of $7D4. Last two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 119 "VEHICLE IGNITION STATUS  $xxxx – bitmap: ignition status  This ID stores the current state of the vehicle’s ignition system, not to be confused with $122 which stores the command given by the (virtual) ignition switch. Location $22F also contains current vehicle state, stored in a different format which may be more usable.  * this location is highly useful in many different applications *";
CM_ BO_ 121 "BRAKING SYSTEM  $x???0??????? – Vehicle is stopped? bitmap $?xxx0??????? – Brake System pressure  $????0xxx???? – Brake Pedal pressure $????0???xxxx – Vehicle speed (MPH x 200)  Three values, and the last two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 123 "GAS PEDAL / THROTTLE VALVE  $xxx???0??? – gas pedal $???x??0??? – unknown, nibble $????xx0??? – unknown, byte $??????0xxx – throttle valve motor  The first value contains the position of the driver’s gas pedal. The fourth value contains the position of the computer-controlled throttle valve motor.  Before using the first value, subtract $c80. Before using the fourth value, subtract $800.";
CM_ BO_ 124 "4xe electric power 0 - 8 bit driving power used 1 - driving status 2 - driving status 4,5 - 16 bit power used / charged";
CM_ BO_ 125 "UNKNOWN  $xx????00???? – bitmap, byte $??xx??00???? – bitmap, byte $????xx00???? – unknown, byte $??????00xxxx – value, word  The last value might have a zero-point at or near $02F8.";
CM_ BO_ 127 "ROTATION OF INDIVIDUAL TIRES  $xx?????? – front driver tire $??xx???? – front passenger tire $????xx?? – rear driver tire $??????xx – rear passenger tire  Units of rotation are unknown. Each value will wrap-around upon hitting $ff.";
CM_ BO_ 129 "UNKNOWN VARIABLES  $xxxx??62????00ff – bitmap, word $????xx62????00ff – value, byte $??????62xx??00ff – value, byte $??????62??xx00ff – value, byte  guess: transmission torque?";
CM_ BO_ 131 "UNKNOWN  $xx0400?????? – unknown, byte $??0400xxxx?? – bitmap, word $??04000000xx – value, byte  Last two bytes are counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 133 "CURRENT GEAR / UNKNOWN VALUES  [0] - Binary - Wet Clutch Status [1] - Gear 4 bit Command - Current [2] - Binary - Status? [3,4] - Torque ? [5,6] - Input RPM";
CM_ BO_ 135 "UNKNOWN  - NOT Braking - Gas Engine ONLY  $xxxx00000??? – value, word $????00000x?? – unknown, nibble $????00000?xx – value, byte  The last two bytes are a counter and a checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 137 "UNKNOWN AIR/FUEL VALUES?  $xxxx???????????? – commanded value $????xxxx???????? – complex bitmap $????????xxxx???? – commanded value $????????????xxxx -- unknown";
CM_ BO_ 139 "INDIVIDUAL TIRE SPEED (MPH)  $xxxx???????????? – Frnt Drvr tire $????xxxx???????? – Frnt Psgr tire $????????xxxx???? – Rear Drvr tire $????????????xxxx – Rear Psgr tir  UNITS: 0.05 MPH, divide by (decimal) 20 to arrive at actual Miles Per Hour";
CM_ BO_ 141 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $C6C0FFFFFFFFFFFF Wrangler 2: $C6C0FFFFFFFFFFFF Wrangler 3: $C6C0FFFFFFFFFFFF";
CM_ BO_ 145 "UNKNOWN  $0xxxxx?????? - bitmap $0?????xxxxxx – unclear format  Last two bytes are counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 147 "Manual / Auto TRANSMISSION   $xx????0000?? – bitmap, byte $??xx??0000?? – bitmap, byte $????xx0000?? – Gear Selection (see notes)";
CM_ BO_ 149 "ENGINE LOAD OR … ?  $xxxx000000 - analog value, word  Last two bytes contain a counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 155 "UNKNOWN  $xx??????00??00FF – bitmap $??xx????00??00FF – value $????xx??00??00FF – bitmap $??????xx00??00FF – bitmap $????????00xx00FF – bitmap  The third byte is a bitmap which occasionally changes to $04 for a while and then it goes back to it's original value of $00.";
CM_ BO_ 157 "UNKNOWN - Throttle position?  $xx – analog value, byte";
CM_ BO_ 167 "UNKNOWN BRAKING VARIABLE  $00000xxx4??? – analog value $00000???4xxx – analog value";
CM_ BO_ 171 "AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION GEAR  $????xx?? -- previous gear $???????x -- current/active gear  Assumed to be the internal state of a double-clutched automatic transmission.";
CM_ BO_ 173 "UNKNOWN  $xx – bitmap ($01,$02, or $04), byte";
CM_ BO_ 177 "CRUISE CONTROL BUTTONS  $xx=cruise control buttons (0=none pressed)  value & 0x40 = center Cruise button value & 0x10 = right Resume button value & 0x08 = bottom Set- button value & 0x04 = top Set+ button value & 0x01 = left Cancel button  The final two bytes are counter and checksum.";
CM_ BO_ 179 "UNKNOWN  $0000xxxx???? – analog val, word $0000????xxxx – bitmap, word";
CM_ BO_ 181 "ENGINE RPMs  $0000xxxx00000000 – engine RPMs, word";
CM_ BO_ 221 "DISTANCE TRAVELLED PER AXLE  $xxxx????00000000 – front axle distance? $????xxxx00000000 – rear axle distance?  two variables, both words, when increase in near-unison as the vehicle moves. With each mile driven, their values become slightly more and more out-of-sync.";
CM_ BO_ 289 "UNKNOWN - Air / Fuel / Etc ?  $xx00????00 – bitmap, byte $??00xx??00 – value,byte $??00??xx00 – bitmap?, byte";
CM_ BO_ 293 "UNKNOWN  $00xx00 – unknown, byte - Temperature?";
CM_ BO_ 295 "TEMPERATURES / OTHER  $xx????00??????00 – Intake Air Temperature  $??xx??00??????00 –  Engine Coolant Temperature  $????xx00??????00 – Barometric Pressure  $??????00xx????00 –  rapid rise to $Ex where it stays  $??????00??xx??00 – likely bitmap, either $00 or $80 $80 causes next value to rise $00 causes next value to fall  $??????00????xx00 – falls to starting value Rises as high as $a2 (162 decimal)";
CM_ BO_ 296 "POWER STEERING PUMP  $00xx???????????? – Fluid Temp in C $00??xx?????????? – Pressure? or...                                       Flow Rate? Current? $00????xx???????? -- Unknown Variable 1 $00??????xxxx???? -- Unknown Variable 2 $00??????????xxxx -- Unknown Variable 3";
CM_ BO_ 297 "UNKNOWN  $xx000000 – unknown bitmap, byte";
CM_ BO_ 299 "UNKNOWN -  $xx1???????ff?? – unknown $??1xxxxxxxff?? – unknown $??1???????ffxx – unknown, byte  You can use this presence of this message (ID 12B with 8 bytes of data) to confirm that you’re reading data from the CAN-C bus.";
CM_ BO_ 301 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $000F000000FF0000 Wrangler 2: $000F000000FF0000 Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 305 "UNKNOWN – REMOTE START?  A series of 10 values appearing only at the time of a remote start, lasts .1 seconds";
CM_ BO_ 307 "REMOTE DOOR LOCK STATUS READ-ONLY (no writes)  ????????xx??????  00=last used to lock some/all doors 20=locking some/all doors NOW 40=last used to unlock driver door 50=unlocking driver door NOW 80=last used to unlock all doors 90=unlocking all doors NOW  It shows if it is actively being used to lock/unlock doors. It also reports how this feature was last used (and not what the current door lock status actually is).";
CM_ BO_ 311 "UNKNOWN  $xx?0000000?????? – unknown $??x0000000?????? – unknown $???0000000xxx??? – unknown $???0000000???xxx – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 315 "4xe Power & Modes  0 - Binary status 1 - unknown 2 - unknown 3 - unknown 4 - 8 bit power used with charging 5 - unknown";
CM_ BO_ 317 "Engine Oil Temp / Pressure / Unknown  $xxxx???????????? – unknown $????xx?????????? – Oil Pressure  (($value * 4) * 0.145038) to PSI $??????xx???????? – Oil Temperature ((($value - 40) * (9 / 5)) + 32) to F $????????xxxx???? – unknown $????????????xxxx – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 319 "UNKNOWN - Battery / Charging / IBS ?  $xxxx???????????? – unknown $????xxxx???????? – unknown $????????xxxx???? – unknown $????????????xxxx – unknown  Interesting numbers, but I cannot place what they’re for.";
CM_ BO_ 321 "4xe Power / battery / Modes  [0] - binary status [2] - binary 4xe modes [4] - 8 bit power used with charging and HVAC [5] - something decending, low res [6] - binary status [7] - unknown";
CM_ BO_ 323 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000000000000000 Wrangler 2: $0000000000000000 Wrangler 3: $0000000000000000";
CM_ BO_ 333 "UNKNOWN  $xx00??00??????00 – unkwn, byte $??00xx00??????00 – unkwn, byte $??00??00xxxxxx00 – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 334 "UNKNOWN  $xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx – complex,data?";
CM_ BO_ 343 "UNKNOWN  $a0000000x0000000  – nibble";
CM_ BO_ 347 "UNKNOWN  $0A0B0C0D0Fxxxxxx – runtime?";
CM_ BO_ 417 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: (none) Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: $0000800000000000";
CM_ BO_ 448 "REMOTE CONTROL COMMANDS  $000000800000 – none (idle) $210000900000 – keyfob lock $230000900000 - 1st press fob unlock $240000900000 - 2nd press fob unlock $2E0000900000 – keyfob panic button $410000800000 – unknown $430000800000 – driver keyless entry $5B0000800000 – unknown $6A0000800000 – (any) cancel rem start $690000800000 – keyfob remote start $810000880000 – app lock doors $830000880000 – app unlock doors $830000880000 – app panic button  can-c should be used to send vehicle commands. stat";
CM_ BO_ 456 "UNKNOWN – KEYFOB RELATED  Personal keyfob id? Keyless Entry / Remote Start";
CM_ BO_ 462 "UNKNOWN  $xx00 – variable, byte  The last two bytes contain a counter and checksum values.";
CM_ BO_ 464 "UNKNOWN  $xxxxxxxx – apparent bitmap  First byte toggles every second between $40 and $C2. The remaining bytes are typically stable, with occasional bit flips.";
CM_ BO_ 469 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000800000000000 Wrangler 2: $0000800000000000 Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 503 "UNKNOWN AND VEHICLE SPEED  $ffffxxxx0080???? – variable, word $ffff????xx?????? [4] - 4xe battery? $ffff????0080xxxx – speed, word";
CM_ BO_ 505 "4xe battery / Power  [0] - power , mid center [1] - power , mid center, combined loads [2] - power, mid center, Starter/Generator [3] - power, HVAC, 0 base [4] - Battery Percent [5] - power , mid center, low res [7] - power , 0 base, gas engine";
CM_ BO_ 516 "UNKNOWN  The locations appear to team up, sending data once or twice per drive. Activates each time with a cluster of three to five messages which spans (or reuses) this group of IDs.";
CM_ BO_ 557 "UNKNOWN VEHICLE STATUS  $xx???????? – variable, byte $??xxxxxxxx – bitmap";
CM_ BO_ 560 "HVAC CONTROLS (READ-ONLY)  $xx??????00000000 – maintains and holds a single digit number, usually (decimal) 8 or 9. Will be 0 when vehicle first turns on.  $??xx????00000000 – Unknown maintains and holds a single digit number, usually (decimal) 3 to 0.  $????xx??00000000 – a value seen smoothly floating up and down in a range between (decimal) 46 and 131  $??????xx00000000 – a number typically centered around (decimal) 50 that makes an occasional jump up or down in a narrow range (usually but no";
CM_ BO_ 562 "AXLE DISTANCE TRAVELED UNKNOWN TEMPERATURE,  $??xx???????? – unknown, temp? $????xxxx???? -- distance 1 $????????xxxx – distance 2  Similar values found at id $0DD";
CM_ BO_ 584 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF Wrangler 2: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF Wrangler 3: $0000FFFFFF03FFFF";
CM_ BO_ 599 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $FF0F003636360000 Wrangler 2: $FF0F003636360000 Wrangler 3: $FF0F003636360000";
CM_ BO_ 601 "FRONT SEAT OCCUPANT SENSORS?  $xxxx00000000 – bitmap, word  Last two bytes contain counter and checksum values.";
CM_ BO_ 605 "AUDIO STATUS / LOCKER REQUEST  ??????xx???????? – 03=mute 00=normal  additional functions possible";
CM_ BO_ 607 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $000002000100003f Wrangler 2: $0000020000000000 Wrangler 3: $0000000100000246";
CM_ BO_ 609 "UNKNOWN ENCODED TIME  $xxxxxxxxxxxx00?? – unknown $????????????00xx – unknown  Appears to count time (perhaps also date) in a slightly encoded (but decipherable) format. The value changes every other update (two seconds).";
CM_ BO_ 611 "UNKNOWN 4xe  [1] - counting up while driving [2] - binary [3] - counting up while driving, extra bit on [2] [4] - possible temperature [6] - binary status [7] - binary status";
CM_ BO_ 613 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $00000000003F0600 Wrangler 2: $00000000003F0600 Wrangler 3: $0000000000000600";
CM_ BO_ 621 "4xe ECH  [0] - power for something % PID loop [2] - binary constant [3] - Power Use, 0 base, Coolant Heater [4] - temperature";
CM_ BO_ 623 "SWAY BAR REQUEST  Wrangler 3: $0040FFFFFF7F7F7F - sway Gladiator 1: $0040FF16447F7F7F - sway  Second byte: \"40\" is seen as the Sway Bar button is pressed, returned to $00 when released.  Fifth byte: Appears to increase/decrease from $40 to $5A after hitting the traction control button.  Also noticed some changes similar to what is seen in location $261. Message rate varied from one to four times per second.";
CM_ BO_ 631 "4X4 STATUS AND AXLE DISCONNECT  $xx????000000??00 - 4x4 transfer case status 0x00 - 2x4 HI 0x10 - 4x4 HI 0x20 - Neutral 0x40 - 4x4 LO 0x80 - 4x4 in transition  $??xx??000000??00 - transfer case neutral selected 0x00 - in gear 0x02 - in neutral  $??00xx000000??00 - front axle disconnect status 0x4C - axle disconnected 0x0C - axle connected  $??00??000000xx00 – vehicle init 0xC0 - vehicle init 0x00 - vehicle on  Returns a constant value, with only a slight variation for one or two seconds while th";
CM_ BO_ 633 "UNKNOWN ENCODED TIME  $xxxxxxxxxx000000 – unknown  The second byte increases every 91 seconds. Also saw an increase on the fifth byte after an unknown interval.";
CM_ BO_ 634 "UNKNOWN DECREASING AND INCREASING NUMBERS.  $00xx0000??????07 – slowly decs FUEL level? $00??0000xxxxxx07 – increases  The first number is small and decreases slowly. Mileage remaining? The second number is big and may be something like a tripometer.";
CM_ BO_ 635 "UNKNOWN NUMBER  $A0xx000000000000 – floating num";
CM_ BO_ 641 "UNKNOWN NUMBERS  $xx??001E0001007C – unknown $??xx001E0001007C – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 643 "UNKNOWN NUMBERS  $000800xx00??0000 – unknown $000800??00xx0000 – unknown";
CM_ BO_ 649 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $3000071ED0218000 Wrangler 1: $3000071ED0158000 Wrangler 2: $3000071EC0150000 Wrangler 3: $3000071ED0218000";
CM_ BO_ 650 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $00000000003f0000 Wrangler 2: (none) Wrangler 3: (none)";
CM_ BO_ 651 "UNKNOWN CONSTANT  Wrangler 1: $00000000001E0000 Wrangler 2: $00000000001E0000 Wrangler 3: $00000000001E0000";
CM_ BO_ 656 "UNKNOWN RARE NUMBER  $xxxxxxxx – unknown  An unknown number that appears twice during a drive, and may be increasing with each drive.";
CM_ BO_ 657 "VEHICLE LIGHTS  $?x?????????????? value&0x4=fogs on $?????x?????????? value&0x1=running lghts $??????x????????? value&0x4=left blinker                                    value&0x8=right blinker $???????????x???? value&0x1=cabin lights $????????????xx?? interior dimmer value $???????????????x value&0x2 headlights on $???????????????x value&0x4 brights on  Some updates (brights) are reported as they happen. Others (fog lights) are updated in their regular 1 second interval.  Values for the interio";
CM_ BO_ 662 "TIRE PRESSURE?  $xx0083????????ff – unknown ive seen 0x20 and 0x40  $??0083xx??????ff - Tire pressure Left Front PSI $??0083??xx????ff - Tire pressure Right Front PSI $??0083????xx??ff - Tire pressure Left Rear PSI $??0083??????xxff - Tire pressure Right Rear PSI  The first value seems like a bitmap. The second value is actually a collection of four individual bytes.  Every now and then, one of them will flip up or down to the next number, and soon after, the other three bytes usually follow the";
CM_ BO_ 663 "UNKNOWN  $F0FF0300000C24FF – startup $F0FF0300000C00FF – otherwise  Aside from a quick blip when the vehicle wakes up, this acts like a constant.";
CM_ BO_ 673 "UNKNOWN BITMAP  Wrangler 1: $8008FCF329FE7DFE Wrangler 1: $0008FCF321FE71FE Wrangler 1: $8008FCF029FE7DFE Wrangler 1: $0008FCF311FE21FE Wrangler 2: $8008FCF329FE7DFE Wrangler 3: $8008FCF0A9FE7DFE";
CM_ BO_ 676 "UNKNOWN  $00xx00??0000 – changing val $00??00xx0000 – bitmap?  Last two bytes are a counter and checksum.";
